 dynamics into encoder-decoder interaction, enabling the model to learn *when* and *how much* to rely on early vs. late encoder states, depending on the complexity of the current decoding step. This is especially valuable for tasks involving multi-step reasoning or long-range dependencies, where different parts of the output may depend on different stages of encoder abstraction.

